// Stdlib: Trajectory Input Shaping  (`std.trajectory`)
//
// PRD: docs/prds/v0_3/trajectory-input-shaping.md §4.1, §11 task α.
//
// Provides the named-type substrate for the v0.3 trajectory-input-shaping
// PRD — every consumer task (β / δ / η / ι / ξ) depends on the trait, enum,
// and structure_def names declared here. Scope is the type surface only —
// no Rust evaluator and no constructor side effects (that is β).
//
// Surface (PRD §4.1):
//   - trait Profile                     (marker for all motion-profile variants)
//   - trait BoundaryCondition           (marker for all spline boundary kinds)
//   - enum  SplineKind                  (CubicSpline | QuinticSpline)
//   - structure def Waypoint            (t, values, vels?, accels?)
//   - structure def NaturalSpline       (zero-DOF marker : BoundaryCondition)
//   - structure def ClampedSpline       (start_velocity, end_velocity : BoundaryCondition)
//   - structure def PeriodicSpline      (zero-DOF marker : BoundaryCondition)
//   - structure def PiecewisePolynomialProfile : Profile
//                                       (mechanism, waypoints, boundary, spline_kind;
//                                        constraint waypoints.count > 0)
//
// Module placement: registered last in `stdlib_loader.rs` — `std.trajectory`
// has no compile-time dependency on any other stdlib module (every type it
// references is a primitive, builtin parametric container, the `Time`
// dimension from `std.units`, or a name declared in this file). The trailing
// position keeps the v0.3 trajectory cluster visually grouped at the end of
// the loader, ready for the planned `std.modal` / `std.dynamics` siblings.
//
// Encoding notes:
//   1. `JointValue` is declared as a `pub type JointValue = Real` alias at
//      the top of the file so call sites read `List<JointValue>` exactly
//      matching the PRD §4.1 declaration. The kinematic-constraints
//      completion PRD (sibling, not yet landed) will replace the underlying
//      `Real` with a proper kinematic-scalar type; that single alias line
//      retargets every consumer in this file without touching any
//      structure_def body. Same posture as `analysis.ri::pub type Stress =
//      Pressure` and `pub type Strain = Dimensionless`.
//   2. `mechanism` on `PiecewisePolynomialProfile` uses bare `Real` with a
//      `TODO(mechanism-type)` note pointing at the same sibling PRD. No
//      analogous alias makes sense (Mechanism is a structural type, not a
//      scalar dimension) — same pattern as `LoadCase.loads : List<Real>`'s
//      `TODO(load-trait)` annotation in `fea_multi_case.ri`.

// ── Type aliases ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

// JointValue: per-joint scalar — position / velocity / acceleration depending
// on the call-site. Currently aliased to `Real` as the kinematic-completion
// PRD (which owns the proper kinematic-scalar type) has not landed yet.
// Same placeholder convention as `fea_multi_case.ri::LoadCase.loads :
// List<Real>` with its `TODO(load-trait)` annotation. Retargeting this line
// when the kinematic PRD lands propagates the type tightening to every
// consumer in this file without touching any structure_def body.
//
// TODO(joint-value-type): retarget to the kinematic-completion PRD's
// `JointValue` (likely `Scalar<...>` or a struct) when that PRD lands.
pub type JointValue = Real

// ── Marker traits ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

// Profile — marker trait for every motion-profile variant (PRD §4.1).
// Currently only `PiecewisePolynomialProfile` refines it; future variants
// (TrapezoidalProfile, SCurveProfile, …) are queued in later v0.3 phases.
//
// Kept empty by design: every shared member would force every variant to
// carry redundant data and defeat the marker-trait purpose. Future shared
// fields (e.g. `total_duration`) land in their own phases once the design
// has settled on a single representation.
trait Profile { }

// BoundaryCondition — marker trait for every spline boundary-mode variant
// (PRD §4.1). The α phase declares three refining structures:
//   - NaturalSpline   ("zero second derivative at endpoints")
//   - ClampedSpline   ("specified tangents at first / last waypoint")
//   - PeriodicSpline  ("first and last waypoint agree")
//
// Kept empty: each variant encodes its semantic invariant in the β-phase
// evaluator (`PiecewisePolynomialProfile` coefficient construction), not as
// an authoring-time param. The trait exists only to give the `boundary`
// param on `PiecewisePolynomialProfile` a single nominal type so the
// evaluator dispatches on the concrete variant via the SIR-α nominal
// type-tag — exactly the same mechanism `solve_elastic_static` uses to
// dispatch on `PointLoad` vs `FixedSupport`.
trait BoundaryCondition { }

// ── Spline degree selector ────────────────────────────────────────────────

// SplineKind — selects the polynomial degree the β evaluator uses when
// building the per-segment coefficients for a `PiecewisePolynomialProfile`
// (PRD §4.1):
//
//   CubicSpline   — degree-3 polynomial per segment; the default when
//                   waypoints carry only positions (vels / accels are none).
//   QuinticSpline — degree-5 polynomial per segment; selected when waypoints
//                   carry explicit `vels` AND `accels` (per-waypoint q̇ and q̈
//                   give the extra degrees of freedom a quintic needs).
//
// Same module-top-level positioning as `enum HardnessScale` in
// `materials_mechanical.ri`.
enum SplineKind { CubicSpline, QuinticSpline }

// ── Waypoint ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

// Waypoint — per-knot data the spline interpolates between (PRD §4.1).
//
//   t       : Time                          — knot time
//   values  : List<JointValue>              — per-joint positions
//   vels    : Option<List<JointValue>>      — optional per-joint q̇
//   accels  : Option<List<JointValue>>      — optional per-joint q̈
//
// No defaults — every field is caller-supplied (the spline path through the
// waypoints is entirely determined by the caller's data). `vels` / `accels`
// are `Option`-typed so the caller can omit per-knot derivative data when
// the chosen `SplineKind` does not need it (cubic interpolation works with
// positions alone; quintic needs both).
//
// No structure-level constraint: the only meaningful cross-field invariant
// (`vels.len() == values.len()` when present) is owned by the β-phase
// profile builder once it sees all waypoints together — a per-knot constraint
// cannot see the rest of the waypoint list, so the check belongs there.
//
// TODO(joint-value-type): `List<JointValue>` retargets to the kinematic-
// completion PRD's proper `JointValue` type when that PRD lands (see the
// header §1 type alias note).
structure def Waypoint {
    param t : Time
    param values : List<JointValue>
    param vels : Option<List<JointValue>>
    param accels : Option<List<JointValue>>
}
